Implements the migrate command that was planned since the initial jj colocation work. Resolves the last missing piece: notes on rewritten commits can now be bulk-reattached via change_id edges. The jj fallback read (single-note lookup) was already working; this adds the batch operation.

Design choices:
- --map file as escape hatch for non-jj use or scripted pipelines
- Move semantics (not copy) — old note is removed after reattach
- Conflict = skip, not error — safe for concurrent note-writers
- Idempotent — safe to run repeatedly after rebases
